				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Sinister Strikes<a name="51384"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 12 04 11:58 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Right - it adds to the damage bonus.  On your main hand, at 65, you get 13 more points of damage added to every hit.  But there is a 0 bonus to offhand which is why your off hand sometimes hits for 1 or 2 pts of damage even if you have a good weapon there.  Sinister Strikes adds 5 ts of damage bonus to off hand -- damage directly added to each hit.  So an offhand hit for 10 would become 15.  It does not change the damage rating of the weapon.  It changes the bonus.
<br />

<br />
While 5 pts of damage per offhand hit may not seem a lot, it does add up eventually.  If you have a fast off-hand and maxed dual wield, I can easily see it adding about 70 or 80 damage per minute.  10% to overall DPS seems unlikely to me, based on the math there.  That would be a LOT of offhand hits -- something on the order of one hit per second.  My offhand doesn't hit anywhere NEAR that often.  I think 3 to 5% added DPS is more believable.</span></td>
