				<td colspan="2"><span>precisly, this is what SS does.  It adds 5 dmg per hit to your offhand.  If your offhand currently hit for 100, it'll hit for 105.  
<br />

<br />
And to calculate it's dps in a simple manner...
<br />

<br />
assuming you have a 20 dly weapon, hasted at 100%, you'll hit 60 times/min, assuming your DW check is 100%.  It's usually a lilttle lower, say, 80%, so you hit 60*.8=48 times a min.  Also, in that 48 times you swing, you miss about 40% of the time (yay?), so you have....  say, 30 times left.  in each of that 30 times that you actually hit your target with offhand weapons, with a 20 dly weapon, every minute, you gain 30*5=150 dmg.  150 dmg/min is about 2.5 DPS.  You can multiply that by 1.3 for overhaste, and 1.2 for WA, when it's fixed.  but after all, the gain is less than 5 dps, for a bard.  </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
