				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Sinister Strikes<a name="60152"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 3 04 4:17 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If the theory is that this adds 5 damage to any off-hand hit, then...
<br />

<br />
- If I were to hit a mob 30 times/minute with my off-hand weapon, thats...
<br />
30hits X 5 damage = 150 damage/minute
<br />
150dmg / 60 seconds = 2.5 damage/second
<br />

<br />
- If I were to hit a mob 60 times/minute with off-hand weapon, thats...
<br />
60hits X 5 damage = 300 damage/minute
<br />
300dmg / 60 seconds = 5 damage/second
<br />

<br />
Conclusion: The number of times a minute you are able to 'hit' a mob with off-hand weapon determines how useful this AA is.
<br />

<br />
- Weapon 'delay' can never drop below 10
<br />
- A delay of 10 = 1 second real time
<br />

<br />
Conclusion: The most a player can 'swing' in 1 minute is 60 times (per weapon). Under single attack, fastest hit conditions, thats a max of 5dps.
<br />

<br />
- Some classes get double/tripple attack as a skill or via AA.  This would further increase the dps.
<br />

<br />
- Critical hits would further increase the DPS
<br />
- Standard crit hits are double the damage it would have done, so it would add 10 to the crit, instead of 5.
<br />
- Some crit hits, like crippling blows are 3-4x greater, making it 15-20 more damage/hit.
<br />

<br />
- Riposte: not 100% sure, but I think you can riposte with off-hand.  If so, this would also increase effectiveness.
<br />

<br />
65 Bard, with epic in off-hand, In plane of earth, shammy haste, and 30% over-haste (most of the time)
<br />
Harmonious attack 5, Ambidexterity, Combat Fury 1 - 1500ATK
<br />
Delay was approx 14 , or 1.4 seconds (but this does not mean I actually landed an attack every 1.4 seconds).
<br />
I landed 30 hits/minute. (only crit 1%, so lets not count crits)
<br />
It would have added (30hits X 5dam) / 60 sec = 2.5 dps
<br />

<br />
While it would take a great deal of other AA's and a faster weapon to make this 'worth' 15 AA for a bard, other classes will eat it up. Would love to see parses from a Warrior/Ranger/Rogue.
<br />

<br />
P.S.
<br />
If you're looking to increase DPS, try Spell Casting Fury 3 and a few weapon procs from LDoN. (I also have Weapon Affinity 4)
<br />
Weapon 1: (droppable - 20-30k in bazaar) 14/28 - (innate) 625 proc - (LDoN) 150 proc
<br />
Weapon 2: 16/27 - Epic proc - (LDoN) 125 proc
<br />

<br />
I get about 40-60dps from that combo.  Both weapons yield 25-35 dps each + 40-80dps from procs.  Average about 90-100 DPS per fight, sometimes up to 140 dps for sustained periods. 
<br />

<br />
- Zoultan Izevhil
<br />
&quot;d*mn it feels good to be a bard and crit proc for 1250 points of damage&quot;.</span></td>
